# printInteractionControllerDidFinishJob(_:)

**Instance Method**

Tells the delegate that the print job has ended.

## Declaration

```swift
@MainActor optional func printInteractionControllerDidFinishJob(_ printInteractionController: UIPrintInteractionController)
```

## Parameters

- **printInteractionController**: The shared instance of [doc://com.apple.uikit/documentation/UIKit/UIPrintInteractionController] that is managing the print job.

## Discussion

You can implement this method to do clean-up tasks related to the print job. This method is called after the last page of the print job is generated but before the completion handler (a block handler of type [doc://com.apple.uikit/documentation/UIKit/UIPrintInteractionController/CompletionHandler]) is called.

## Responding to the Start and End of a Print Job

- **printInteractionControllerWillStartJob(_:)**: Tells the delegate that the print job is about to start.
